            </span></span></h1></div><div xmlns:x="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:local="http://syriaca.org/ns"><div style="margin:0 1em 1em; color: #999999;"><small><p><span class="srp-label"><strong>Syriaca.org URI</strong></span>: <span id="syriaca-id"><a href="http://syriaca.org/place/2698">http://syriaca.org/place/2698</a></span></p></small></div></div><div xmlns:x="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:local="http://syriaca.org/ns" class="row"><div class="col-md-8"><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent"> Because Musonius had fled from Meloe, and Paul had left
                                Olba,
                                Severus
                            advised Solon
                            to appoint new bishops, or at the very least to petition the emperor to
                            assemble a council of bishops in Isauria.  <a href="/3052-13" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Last year, Severus compelled
                                bishop Paul of
                                    Olba to return to his flock.  <a href="/3046-30" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Between
                                515 and 517, Severus wrote a letter to Solon, bishop of Seleucia in Isauria concerning the
                            absence of Paul of
                                    Olba's absence.  <a href="/3055-6" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> Because Paul had been long absent from his bishopric in
                                Olba,
                                Severus
                            urged Solon to
                            replace him.  <a href="/3055-7" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/></div><div class="sources"><h4>Personal Names: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-listPerson">
